Summary: 2 separate objects at sunrise a distance apart. Both different shapes.
divs: Sighting DetailsI was awake early and stood on my balcony to watch the sunrise and noticed 2 shining objects which I thought may be satelites and so I took a picture of both before the sun came over the horizon. When the sub rose over the horizon, it was not possible to see either one. When I look at one photo, the object looks possibly saucer shaped and the other is difficult to decipher. Perhaps with a better viewer enhancer there will be a better shape. One last picture (4) is just before the sunrise.
trends: There have been no other sightings in Fuengirola
